The '''Bor massacre''' was a massacre of an estimated 2,000 civilians in [[Bor, South Sudan|Bor]] on November 15, 1991 during the [[Second Sudanese Civil War]]. The massacre<ref>[[Richard Cockett]] Sudan: Darfur and the failure of an African state. 2010. Hobbs the Printers Ltd, Totton, Hampshire. {{ISBN|978-0-300-16273-8}}</ref> was carried out mostly by [[Nuer people|Nuer]] fighters from [[SPLA-Nasir]], led by [[Riek Machar]], and the militant group known as the [[Nuer White Army]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-25543061|title=South Sudan: White Army 'abandons war march' on Bor town|publisher=bbcnews.com|accessdate=29 December 2013|date=29 December 2013}}</ref> [[Amnesty International]] said at least 2,000 Dinka were killed, though the real number may have been higher.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-25454168|title=Tangled web of South Sudan politics spells bleak future|publisher=bbcnews.com|accessdate=20 December 2013|date=19 December 2013}}</ref> In the years which followed, an estimated 25,000<ref name=eveningpost/> more died from [[famine]] as their cattle were either stolen or shot and the fighting had displaced them from the land they had once cultivated.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/programmes/from_our_own_correspondent/5133324.stm|title=Reclaiming the past in Southern Sudan|publisher=bbcnews.com|accessdate=20 December 2013|date=1 July 2006}}</ref> At the time, Riek Machar described the incident as "propaganda" and "myth".<ref name=eveningpost>{{cite news|url=http://www.thelondoneveningpost.com/riek-machar-breaks-down-in-tears-as-he-admits-to-1991-bor-massacres/|title=Riek Machar in tears as he admits to 1991 Bor massacres|publisher=thelondoneveningpost.com|accessdate=20 December 2013|date=16 August 2011}}</ref> In 2012, he publicly apologized for his part in the massacre.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sudantribune.com/spip.php?article42124|title=South Sudan VP confirms apology for Bor Massacre|publisher=sudantribune.com|accessdate=20 December 2013|date=4 April 2012}}</ref><ref>You Tube [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Qg8tD4qGpOk Channel 4 UK TV Report by Mark Stucke Nov 1991]</ref><ref>[[Sudan Tribune]] August 31, 2007 http://www.sudantribune.com/spip.php?article23545. By Gatkuoth Lam. [[Dinka]] [[Bor, South Sudan|Bor]] [[Massacre]]</ref>
